posts.title: Hello World
posts.description: Once you have done this, you can start creating pages in the src/pages folder. For example, to create a new page called home, you would create a file called home.js in the src/pages folder.
posts.body_1: Creating a folder to hold the pages folder can be a good way to organize your application code, especially if you have a large number of pages. It can also make it easier to share code between pages, as you can easily move pages and their associated components between folders.
